02:10:54,267 --> 02:10:57,981
I don't take to strangers too well

1454
02:10:59,733 --> 02:11:02,234
But I don't know..

1455
02:11:04,867 --> 02:11:07,778
I don't know why
the two of you have..

1456
02:11:08,119 --> 02:11:13,663
..touched my heart

1457
02:11:16,416 --> 02:11:20,039
We've done what?
- Touched my heart..

1458
02:11:22,170 --> 02:11:26,544
you could've been my children

1459
02:11:28,255 --> 02:11:31,718
You haven't told us your name.
- You haven't told..

1460
02:11:32,388 --> 02:11:34,639
My name is Dashrath

1461
02:11:35,641 --> 02:11:41,305
Dashrath Singh, Deputy
Commissioner of Police

1462
02:11:41,395 --> 02:11:42,976
You're a police' wallah?

1463
02:11:46,189 --> 02:11:50,063
What did you think? Balloon' wallah?

1464
02:11:54,445 --> 02:11:56,407
Why what's come over you?

1465
02:11:58,158 --> 02:12:00,201
What's it?
- Rickshaw' wallah..

1466
02:12:00,281 --> 02:12:01,992
Sit in the rickshaw

1467
02:12:02,072 --> 02:12:05,165
Go on, take him home.
- Yes, take me home

1468
02:12:05,245 --> 02:12:07,366
It's very late.
- Very late at night

1469
02:12:07,496 --> 02:12:10,619
Take me to the airport..

1470
02:12:10,709 --> 02:12:14,081
no not there

1471
02:12:14,631 --> 02:12:21,257
I'm going to Police Lines.
- Go on, quick

1472
02:12:29,723 --> 02:12:33,847
Oh my God, the very same Dashrath
Singh the one who's been after us?

1473
02:12:35,559 --> 02:12:40,353
My baby almost had a heart attack!
That was close, let's get out of here

1474
02:12:40,733 --> 02:12:48,198
Get out? The fun's only just begun
- What are you talking about?

1475
02:12:51,201 --> 02:12:57,536
Look, he never knew what we look
like. He still doesn't. But now..

1476
02:12:58,366 --> 02:13:02,790
we know who he is
and we also know that..

1477
02:13:03,751 --> 02:13:08,544
he's in charge of the security
of the gold stashed at the airport

1478
02:13:10,877 --> 02:13:14,419
By God! You are..
- Vimmi, if we don't..

1479
02:13:14,509 --> 02:13:17,091
steal the meat right
from the lion's den..

1480
02:13:17,182 --> 02:13:21,095
what did we achieve?
- Your hunger's getting out of hand

1481
02:13:23,636 --> 02:13:29,431
Now we're a threesome. We'll
need more food.. what do you say?

1482
02:13:31,233 --> 02:13:32,644
You'll get us killed someday

1483
02:13:39,399 --> 02:13:41,941
India's Central Bank doesn't
keep its gold in any one place

1484
02:13:42,071 --> 02:13:45,785
To protect the gold from fires,
floods or earthquakes..

1485
02:13:45,905 --> 02:13:48,246
the cache is split
over four different cities

1486
02:13:48,786 --> 02:13:51,409
Depending on the requirements
of various banks..

1487
02:13:51,499 --> 02:13:55,451
this gold is shuttled by air between
these four cities once every week

1488
02:13:57,123 --> 02:14:01,417
How they cracked this confidential
information, they haven't divulged

1489
02:14:02,508 --> 02:14:07,051
But what they did that day no
one could have ever imagined

1490
02:14:08,092 --> 02:14:09,012
Not even me..

1491
02:14:12,385 --> 02:14:16,809
Delhi-Mumbai, 9.10 pm tonight.
Korpal, Puneet, Mr.

1492
02:14:16,889 --> 02:14:23,564
And Delhi-Calcutta, 9.40 pm.
Sharma, Vandana, Mrs.

1493
02:14:24,685 --> 02:14:27,607
What's this other ticket for?
- Backup

1494
02:14:29,489 --> 02:14:39,497
-=MTR=-

1495
02:14:41,789 --> 02:14:44,991
Why the Air Traffic Control number?
- Backup

1496
02:14:45,661 --> 02:14:51,547
A back up for everything? Oye
Rakesh, is there one for you too?

1497
02:14:53,008 --> 02:14:54,879
Yes
- Who?

1498
02:14:56,551 --> 02:14:57,842
You

1499
02:15:00,093 --> 02:15:01,053
Smart

1500
02:16:46,637 --> 02:16:50,841
Call back the Jet airways flight
to Mumbai. The bomb is ticking

1501
02:16:50,931 --> 02:16:54,594
What nonsense. A bomb on the plane?

1502
02:17:00,609 --> 02:17:03,271
Jet 9W312. Yes Delhi Control?

1503
02:17:03,481 --> 02:17:07,275
Turn back and proceed for
landing on emergency runway number 2

1504
02:17:07,365 --> 02:17:08,856
There is a bomb scare

1505
02:17:08,946 --> 02:17:10,406
Delhi Control is this a joke?

1506
02:17:10,487 --> 02:17:11,567
Bomb on board, he says

1507
02:17:11,657 --> 02:17:13,739
Jet 9W312. Turning back

1508
02:17:20,785 --> 02:17:22,035
The caller's number. Get it now

1509
02:17:22,165 --> 02:17:24,168
Go get the number from them. Now!

1510
02:17:24,248 --> 02:17:26,499
We can't have the number

1511
02:17:26,579 --> 02:17:29,962
It isn't under ourjurisdiction.
- As long as the gold is on board..

1512
02:17:30,082 --> 02:17:32,875
this plane, the bomb, this airport,
everything is under our jurisdiction

1513
02:18:20,082 --> 02:18:23,715
How many people knew about
the gold? - Four bank employees

1514
02:18:23,755 --> 02:18:25,376
Are you implying the news was
leaked? - Give me the key to the box

1515
02:18:25,466 --> 02:18:27,337
But we are not permitted to
open it. - Give me the key

1516
02:18:27,467 --> 02:18:29,970
Now it's your responsibility. - The
bomb might explode any time, sir

1517
02:18:30,050 --> 02:18:33,053
The bomb has exploded.
Send message to headquarters.

1518
02:18:33,383 --> 02:18:35,924
I am assuming command

1519
02:18:51,146 --> 02:18:52,939
DCP Dashrath Singh here..

1520
02:18:53,149 --> 02:18:55,030
Surround the airport area

1521
02:18:55,320 --> 02:18:58,533
Locate persons who do not have
any reason to be here at this hour

1522
02:18:59,403 --> 02:19:01,615
Take suspects into
custody and inform immediately

1523
02:19:01,705 --> 02:19:03,827
They received the bomb
scare from this number

1524
02:19:14,716 --> 02:19:16,006
Dial

1525
02:19:20,670 --> 02:19:30,638
Ringing

1526
02:20:38,031 --> 02:20:41,694
Orange Maruti Swift 5700

1527
02:20:47,039 --> 02:20:50,832
Vimmi we'll have to ditch
this car. They've spotted it.

1528
02:20:50,912 --> 02:20:52,373
Get out

1529
02:21:12,809 --> 02:21:14,641
Stop.. taxi

1530
02:21:17,353 --> 02:21:19,645
Stop.. please

1531
02:21:23,437 --> 02:21:25,860
Papa'ji, please help us!

1532
02:21:25,940 --> 02:21:28,191
I'll give you more money
than you ever imagined

1533
02:21:28,321 --> 02:21:32,194
Son, for this job, I won't take
money even if you give it to me..

1534
02:21:32,274 --> 02:21:37,028
come my child, get up,
you'll do fine

1535
02:21:37,158 --> 02:21:40,071
Have faith in god. Faith prevails

1536
02:21:40,201 --> 02:21:42,202
Sir, what are you saying?

1537
02:21:42,873 --> 02:21:45,665
Policemen in every
hospital and nursing home?

1538
02:21:45,745 --> 02:21:47,787
We won't have men
for policing the city.

1539
02:21:48,377 --> 02:21:51,830
She's in labour.
She's about to deliver

1540
02:21:53,381 --> 02:21:58,425
Every child born in Delhi
tonight will see a policeman's face..

1541
02:21:58,505 --> 02:22:00,928
before anything else

1542
02:22:02,639 --> 02:22:06,892
That Dashrath Singh figured me out.

1543
02:22:07,683 --> 02:22:08,973
How are you so sure?

1544
02:22:09,143 --> 02:22:11,936
I know.

1545
02:22:12,727 --> 02:22:14,267
I saw it in his eyes..

1546
02:22:17,731 --> 02:22:18,851
Then..

1547
02:22:19,151 --> 02:22:23,735
in no time every hospital in Delhi
will be crawling with policemen

1548
02:22:25,197 --> 02:22:28,449
Which hospital do
you want to go to son?

1549
02:22:29,871 --> 02:22:32,612
The biggest.. the
biggest hospital in Delhi

1550
02:22:32,702 --> 02:22:37,746
Not a hospital or nursing home,
they'll go to a nondescript clinic

1551
02:22:38,917 --> 02:22:41,750
If l know that Bunty..

1552
02:22:42,330 --> 02:22:45,833
..he'll definitely take
Babli to the biggest hospital

1553
02:22:51,468 --> 02:22:53,799
Vimmi, don't be afraid

1554
02:22:53,889 --> 02:22:56,682
This hospital is packed choc-a-bloc
with newborns and their mothers

1555
02:22:56,762 --> 02:23:01,346
It'll take them ages to check
each bed. But you please hurry it up

1556
02:23:01,436 --> 02:23:04,477
It isn't in my hands, bloody idiot!

1557
02:23:05,149 --> 02:23:07,850
I told you you'll
get us killed someday

1558
02:23:07,940 --> 02:23:09,061
Hush

1559
02:23:09,441 --> 02:23:15,317
But hey, what life did I
have before I met you?

1560
02:23:31,079 --> 02:23:32,960
Is everything all right?
- Yes

1561
02:23:35,293 --> 02:23:36,964
Papa'ji.. if you
weren't here today..

1562
02:23:37,084 --> 02:23:38,665
There would have been someone else

1563
02:23:39,505 --> 02:23:43,008
The Lord up there runs a
regular courier service

1564
02:23:43,719 --> 02:23:47,382
He always provides for ones in need

1565
02:25:22,047 --> 02:25:24,669
Those two have fled the hospital
but they haven't fled Delhi yet

1566
02:25:27,341 --> 02:25:29,133
Seal Delhi, sir

1567
02:25:39,811 --> 02:25:43,894
Papa'ji, all that
you've done for us..

1568
02:25:44,024 --> 02:25:47,267
One honest man would do for another

1569
02:25:49,068 --> 02:25:50,819
Papa'ji, you're kidding me

1570
02:25:52,572 --> 02:25:56,865
By now you must have figured that
we aren't half as honest as we seem

1571
02:25:59,867 --> 02:26:04,030
I don't know what you've done to
make these people hunt you down..

1572
02:26:06,833 --> 02:26:11,247
but I see a simple
honesty in your eyes..

1573
02:26:13,088 --> 02:26:16,421
..take care son

1574
02:26:19,342 --> 02:26:26,299
God bless you.

1575
02:26:51,027 --> 02:26:53,950
For the next week or so
they'll be baying for our blood

1576
02:26:54,030 --> 02:27:00,325
We'll return afterwards.. but
where have you hidden the gold?

1577
02:27:01,285 --> 02:27:03,208
What's your baby, a boy or a girl?

1578
02:27:05,629 --> 02:27:07,001
What will you name your baby?

1579
02:27:08,672 --> 02:27:14,176
Before you think of a name you
need to see the baby at least?

1580
02:27:15,757 --> 02:27:20,221
A day has gone by, have you
even taken one look at your baby?

1581
02:27:21,933 --> 02:27:27,187
Did you hold your child in
your arms, even once.. once even?

1582
02:27:34,902 --> 02:27:38,736
Vimmi, you know we didn't
have any time for these.

1583
02:27:40,567 --> 02:27:41,819
Had l stopped for all this..

1584
02:27:41,949 --> 02:27:44,910
all three of us would've
either been jailed or killed by now

1585
02:27:45,661 --> 02:27:47,113
Some reason for celebration!

1586
02:27:47,783 --> 02:27:51,535
The day he is born.. his parents die

1587
02:27:52,167 --> 02:27:56,169
Cursed fate to be born with!
- Not his fault, is it?

1588
02:27:56,329 --> 02:27:59,002
That's what I'm saying!
What wrong has he done..

1589
02:27:59,132 --> 02:28:03,215
to deserve parents who
can go to jail anytime..

1590
02:28:03,676 --> 02:28:05,337
leaving him to rot on the streets

1591
02:28:10,471 --> 02:28:13,473
What are you trying to say?
- Enough

1592
02:28:15,184 --> 02:28:18,307
I won't do this anymore.
Neither will you..

1593
02:28:22,021 --> 02:28:23,231
Then what else can we do?

1594
02:28:24,022 --> 02:28:28,235
Anything, whatever
everyone else does

1595
02:28:30,487 --> 02:28:32,859
If we had to end up doing
what everybody else does..

1596
02:28:32,949 --> 02:28:34,610
why did we ever run away from home?

1597
02:28:37,203 --> 02:28:38,613
Because we were wrong

1598
02:28:44,708 --> 02:28:48,751
Now we're not free
to live as we like.

1599
02:28:49,872 --> 02:28:52,755
Now we're
responsible for one more life

1600
02:28:53,425 --> 02:28:54,966
How's he going to grow up?

1601
02:28:55,426 --> 02:28:57,167
How? With us..

1602
02:28:57,219 --> 02:28:59,010
..that's how With us?

1603
02:28:59,430 --> 02:29:01,761
And which school will he go to

1604
02:29:02,593 --> 02:29:05,765
You know this world we live in
has two kinds of people. One..

1605
02:29:06,055 --> 02:29:09,768
who waste the best years of
their lives in schools and colleges.

1606
02:29:09,938 --> 02:29:12,481
And the kind who school themselves.

1607
02:29:13,021 --> 02:29:15,933
Like us. We taught us
to do what we're doing

1608
02:29:16,313 --> 02:29:18,275
Which is what he'll learn?
- Of course!

1609
02:29:18,565 --> 02:29:20,356
And then he'll go to jail someday?

1610
02:29:20,696 --> 02:29:22,399
Have we ever been to jail?

1611
02:29:23,149 --> 02:29:26,071
We very nearly got thrown into jail

1612
02:29:27,031 --> 02:29:32,155
I don't want my son
growing up behind bars..

1613
02:29:33,327 --> 02:29:35,328
or dying young on the run

1614
02:29:36,709 --> 02:29:42,203
Do you remember agreeing on
all our marriage vows except..

1615
02:29:42,665 --> 02:29:44,666
We'll be Bunty-Babli
for the rest of our lives

1616
02:29:44,796 --> 02:29:48,669
And we'll live out all our dreams.
- Except..

1617
02:29:49,800 --> 02:29:53,053
Except?
- Leave that to me

1618
02:29:53,673 --> 02:29:54,674
Okay

1619
02:29:55,304 --> 02:29:57,265
This is the exception Rakesh

1620
02:29:58,097 --> 02:30:00,968
You're getting over-emotional
about this motherhood business

1621
02:30:04,892 --> 02:30:08,895
But now l am whatever l am.
Now I want to hear your decision

1622
02:30:09,566 --> 02:30:12,357
Choose. lt's either this life..
or a life together

1623
02:30:29,371 --> 02:30:30,792
So what have you decided?

1624
02:30:35,296 --> 02:30:37,127
What'll I do without the two of you?

1625
02:30:44,884 --> 02:30:46,885
Those marriage vows
weren't mere words

1626
02:30:51,679 --> 02:30:53,311
Fursatganj or Pankinagar?

1627
02:30:55,022 --> 02:30:56,513
Is it you that's saying this or?

1628
02:30:59,355 --> 02:31:00,646
Bunty and Rakesh. Both

1629
02:31:08,733 --> 02:31:10,484
What?
- Tickets

1630
02:31:14,617 --> 02:31:17,159
Since when are we buying tickets?
- From today

1631
02:31:18,871 --> 02:31:20,662
Why become so damn honest?

1632
02:31:30,130 --> 02:31:33,001
Oye Rakesh, you're in love

1633
02:31:35,214 --> 02:31:36,795
Oh all right

1634
02:31:39,717 --> 02:31:46,352
Rakesh my boy, this world we
live in has two kinds of men. One..

1635
02:31:46,392 --> 02:31:48,263
the kind that thinks
twice before getting married

1636
02:31:48,433 --> 02:31:51,476
And the kind that thinks
afterwards like you, you idiot

1637
02:31:54,609 --> 02:31:57,771
Two tickets for Fursatganj

1638
02:31:58,151 --> 02:31:59,363
Name?

1639
02:32:00,073 --> 02:32:01,774
Rakesh Trivedi, Vimmi Trivedi

1640
02:32:05,368 --> 02:32:06,949
Bunty and Babli

1641
02:32:09,621 --> 02:32:12,323
You've had a long run.
You must be tired

1642
02:32:44,059 --> 02:32:45,349
Rakesh.

1643
02:32:50,944 --> 02:32:52,275
Can we have some water?

1644
02:32:54,407 --> 02:32:55,567
Die of thirst dog!

1645
02:32:56,908 --> 02:32:58,609
Not for me. For the two of them

1646
02:33:22,338 --> 02:33:23,839
You won't believe me..

1647
02:33:24,761 --> 02:33:26,802
..but we quit being
crooks half an hour ago

1648
02:33:29,475 --> 02:33:31,096
Absolutely right, I
won't believe you.

1649
02:33:33,267 --> 02:33:35,019
- But if l insist
I'm telling the truth?

1650
02:33:35,149 --> 02:33:39,141
I'll start doing right now what I
had planned to do to you in jail

1651
02:33:41,814 --> 02:33:44,697
Why are you looking at me like
that? - He's telling the truth

1652
02:33:45,277 --> 02:33:48,989
Guaranteed by you,
India's biggest bonafide liar?

1653
02:33:50,201 --> 02:33:51,612
I'm not lying

1654
02:33:51,742 --> 02:33:55,075
A dog's tail insists it became
ramrod straight half an hour ago?

1655
02:33:55,245 --> 02:33:56,866
You're as old as my father..

1656
02:33:58,537 --> 02:34:00,749
..no one's had the cheek
to talk to her like that

1657
02:34:01,120 --> 02:34:04,371
So you respect your elders now,
do you? - And why shouldn't we?

1658
02:34:04,463 --> 02:34:07,004
Now don't tell me you pray
first thing every morning too!

1659
02:34:07,084 --> 02:34:08,465
She does

1660
02:34:08,715 --> 02:34:12,338
So?
- So what!

1661
02:34:13,179 --> 02:34:15,091
Now you pray to your
heart's content in jail!

1662
02:34:15,841 --> 02:34:19,303
It's all your fault now suffer.
- My fault?

1663
02:34:19,555 --> 02:34:22,977
Who's idea was it to go straight?
- It was for a good cause..

1664
02:34:23,097 --> 02:34:25,929
do you want your son to go to jail?
- So where's he going now?

1665
02:34:26,310 --> 02:34:32,774
Now I see how the two of you
have been fooling people for years

1666
02:34:36,648 --> 02:34:38,189
Pappu is hungry

1667
02:34:39,279 --> 02:34:42,492
Pappu? When did we
start calling him Pappu?

1668
02:34:42,742 --> 02:34:44,323
Got to call him something no?

1669
02:34:44,533 --> 02:34:47,196
You're thinking of
the gold all the time

1670
02:34:50,539 --> 02:34:56,003
Let's step outside for a while

1671
02:34:58,044 --> 02:35:00,297
I'm not going anywhere.
- Up

1672
02:35:03,469 --> 02:35:08,383
Darned luck. No one ever caught
us when we were in the thick of it

1673
02:35:09,673 --> 02:35:11,305
But the moment we quit..

1674
02:35:13,767 --> 02:35:16,429
Why did you get into all this?

1675
02:35:22,524 --> 02:35:24,395
I wanted to become
someone important.

1676
02:35:26,027 --> 02:35:27,398
And.. you became?

1677
02:35:29,529 --> 02:35:32,322
You won't understand.
- Why..

1678
02:35:33,863 --> 02:35:35,285
why won't I understand?

1679
02:35:36,575 --> 02:35:38,827
Because he never did.
- Who?

1680
02:35:40,579 --> 02:35:41,910
My father

1681
02:35:45,253 --> 02:35:46,743
He's just like you

1682
02:35:50,417 --> 02:35:52,748
You're trying to con me again

1683
02:36:00,635 --> 02:36:03,596
May l?
- A smoke? Sure..

1684
02:36:06,519 --> 02:36:07,600
Where are you going?

1685
02:36:08,811 --> 02:36:10,763
If she sees me smoking she'll scream

1686
02:36:16,067 --> 02:36:18,108
The child will stay with the mother

1687
02:36:27,576 --> 02:36:29,277
What's the use of crying now?

1688
02:36:31,199 --> 02:36:34,031
Should've considered this
beforehand. - What else to do?

1689
02:36:36,833 --> 02:36:39,875
Become a ticket collector and
collect ten rupee bribes all my life?

1690
02:36:49,593 --> 02:36:50,795
You can come in

1691
02:37:09,689 --> 02:37:11,941
We'll have to make a phone
call to your home or mine

1692
02:37:12,652 --> 02:37:15,313
We certainly can't take him with us.

1693
02:37:15,443 --> 02:37:17,315
No, it won't come to that

1694
02:37:17,736 --> 02:37:19,026
I'll figure something.

1695
02:37:19,116 --> 02:37:21,699
And con ourselves
out of this one too?

1696
02:37:21,829 --> 02:37:23,370
What else to do?

1697
02:37:25,201 --> 02:37:27,323
Take with me to jail..

1698
02:37:27,994 --> 02:37:29,705
..the very son for whose
sake I gave up everything?

1699
02:37:34,459 --> 02:37:36,001
What justice!

1700
02:37:38,092 --> 02:37:40,793
Jails are for reforming.

1701
02:37:41,135 --> 02:37:43,296
And here, three
people are being jailed

1702
02:37:43,386 --> 02:37:46,469
Two of whom have reformed and a
third who's completely innocent

1703
02:37:47,850 --> 02:37:50,971
Don't worry Vimmi.

1704
02:37:51,183 --> 02:37:54,014
I'll crack a plan.
- What plan Rakesh?

1705
02:37:54,354 --> 02:37:56,517
We've run out of plans

1706
02:38:03,022 --> 02:38:05,563
Vimmi do you have any
idea what jails are like?

1707
02:38:11,569 --> 02:38:13,610
How will you spend so
many years inside one?

1708
02:38:17,914 --> 02:38:23,618
Let's do something, l'll
take the blame for everything

1709
02:38:25,919 --> 02:38:29,252
Then you're free to go home
to Fursatganj with the baby

1710
02:38:32,465 --> 02:38:34,797
All you wanted was to become a model

1711
02:38:37,339 --> 02:38:39,300
I dragged you into this whole thing

1712
02:38:44,224 --> 02:38:49,808
You can't even make a
cup of tea for yourself.

1713
02:38:50,519 --> 02:38:53,021
In jail.. how?
- I'll manage Vimmi..

1714
02:38:53,732 --> 02:38:56,695
..don't worry about me

1715
02:38:57,525 --> 02:39:01,107
Have you ever managed
to do anything alone?

1716
02:39:02,949 --> 02:39:08,073
In any case, Bunty is
nothing without Babli

1717
02:39:32,053 --> 02:39:33,343
Get up

1718
02:39:34,054 --> 02:39:35,345
Unlock yourselves..

1719
02:39:36,685 --> 02:39:38,057
I can't do it..

1720
02:39:39,728 --> 02:39:41,729
We're nearing the railway
signal on the outskirts of Delhi

1721
02:39:43,852 --> 02:39:45,683
The train halts
there for two minutes

1722
02:39:47,775 --> 02:39:49,566
The two of..

1723
02:39:50,196 --> 02:39:54,650
the three of you can get
off and go wherever you wish

1724
02:39:56,071 --> 02:39:58,784
No one recognises
Bunty and Babli except me

1725
02:40:01,745 --> 02:40:03,327
And no one ever will

1726
02:40:23,383 --> 02:40:26,345
Sir..
- Shut up. Not a word

1727
02:40:27,677 --> 02:40:29,558
Or l just might change my mind

1728
02:40:31,059 --> 02:40:32,391
Get going

1729
02:40:35,022 --> 02:40:38,775
That's enough

1730
02:41:02,585 --> 02:41:06,297
Whether it was my
life's biggest mistake..

1731
02:41:06,797 --> 02:41:08,919
..or their best con act,
I didn't know

1732
02:41:10,760 --> 02:41:14,304
But policemen are human too,
believe it or not..

1733
02:41:15,674 --> 02:41:17,305
we wear those
uniforms only on our body,

1734
02:41:17,385 --> 02:41:19,928
..at heart we're as
vulnerable as babies

1735
02:41:22,641 --> 02:41:25,892
I believed I had
destroyed Bunty-Babli,

1736
02:41:26,683 --> 02:41:29,145
so l let Rakesh and Vimmi go..

1737
02:41:30,146 --> 02:41:37,693
because l think the law
needs to destroy crime, not lives

1738
02:41:39,153 --> 02:41:42,365
The bank's gold was recovered
from the spot Babli had indicated

1739
02:41:43,327 --> 02:41:47,529
The recoveries continued
for months afterwards..

1740
02:41:47,951 --> 02:41:54,085
monies and valuables
stolen by Bunty and Babli

1741
02:41:54,375 --> 02:41:57,787
I think they had told me
the truth about going back..

1742
02:41:58,089 --> 02:42:02,251
to live respectable,
honest lives like their parents

1743
02:42:10,468 --> 02:42:13,721
Rakesh'ji could you
perhaps increase the pressure

1744
02:42:18,685 --> 02:42:20,356
What a joy

1745
02:42:23,819 --> 02:42:28,193
This world we live in has
two kinds of Pappus. One..

1746
02:42:28,573 --> 02:42:31,024
the kind who obey their
parents and get to eat chocolates

1747
02:42:31,575 --> 02:42:35,868
and the kind that doesn't and
gets locked up inside toilets

1748
02:42:35,948 --> 02:42:37,869
You are?
- The first

1749
02:42:38,831 --> 02:42:40,822
My darling baby

1750
02:42:42,123 --> 02:42:43,785
But he didn't even drink his milk.

1751
02:42:44,625 --> 02:42:45,956
He'll eat the chocolate

1752
02:42:46,587 --> 02:42:49,709
What good are chocolates?
You and your fads

1753
02:42:49,960 --> 02:42:54,043
No, I'm feeling cold..
- Forget the cold. Be fashionable

1754
02:43:00,258 --> 02:43:01,799
What are you teaching Pappu?

1755
02:43:01,889 --> 02:43:07,303
To speak the truth
and pray every morning

1756
02:43:07,393 --> 02:43:10,556
Where's my son? One of his
friends is waiting downstairs

1757
02:43:12,017 --> 02:43:15,600
Friends and folks in
Fursatganj find all the time for fun

1758
02:43:15,730 --> 02:43:19,193
You fix the name of this city.
I'll fix this friend

1759
02:43:23,365 --> 02:43:26,608
My son is genius from..

1760
02:43:27,529 --> 02:43:29,161
childhood

1761
02:43:29,871 --> 02:43:31,112
I am very lucky

1762
02:43:31,662 --> 02:43:34,665
I got a daughter-in-law
who is very very smart

1763
02:43:35,956 --> 02:43:39,919
It's such a joy to know
that our son and his wife..

1764
02:43:39,959 --> 02:43:41,540
..have done things..

1765
02:43:41,630 --> 02:43:44,623
so important that your
department still remembers them

1766
02:43:46,674 --> 02:43:52,299
Never told folks at home
what all you achieved?

1767
02:43:53,549 --> 02:43:56,182
Maybe you should tell us

1768
02:43:58,805 --> 02:44:00,596
Nervous already?

1769
02:44:02,937 --> 02:44:04,519
A scam is in the offing

1770
02:44:06,940 --> 02:44:08,521
Huge scam

1771
02:44:11,484 --> 02:44:12,695
Sir..

1772
02:44:14,607 --> 02:44:18,901
I swear by my son, l've given it up

1773
02:44:20,451 --> 02:44:22,953
I've no idea of what
scams are happening

1774
02:44:24,205 --> 02:44:27,036
For three years now, I'm
following a work-home-work routine

1775
02:44:27,116 --> 02:44:30,499
This scam has got to be stopped.
- Then go ahead and stop it

1776
02:44:36,834 --> 02:44:38,255
We cannot stop it

1777
02:44:39,547 --> 02:44:40,968
Who else can?

1778
02:44:44,931 --> 02:44:46,172
You

1779
02:44:51,306 --> 02:44:55,389
Please save us from this life of
honesty and respectfulness. Please.

1780
02:44:55,519 --> 02:44:57,771
Is it just you, or..
- Both of us.

1781
02:44:59,813 --> 02:45:04,737
I'd choose death over
making mango pickle.

1782
02:45:05,107 --> 02:45:06,988
I'd rather die, Rakesh.

1783
02:45:26,214 --> 02:45:29,707
Have faith in God. Faith prevails.

1784
02:45:31,168 --> 02:45:33,379
One step, two steps,
he steps it up, swings it

1785
02:45:33,509 --> 02:45:35,881
pumps it, struts his stuff.
Meet Bunty.

1786
02:45:38,763 --> 02:45:40,965
Minute by minute,
she turns it up, spins it

1787
02:45:41,055 --> 02:45:43,557
so you can't get enough. Meet Babli.

1788
02:45:49,983 --> 02:45:53,315
Swami.. Bunty Ramaswami.

1789
02:45:53,395 --> 02:45:56,568
Mandalam.. Babli Cholamandalam.

1790
02:45:57,238 --> 02:46:00,901
Bunty Aur Babli Bunty and Babli

1791
02:46:00,991 --> 02:46:02,322
They maybe two,
but they're too much.

1792
02:46:02,402 --> 02:46:05,535
Once upon a time he told me that
he was in the business of cleaning

1793
02:46:05,615 --> 02:46:08,407
So l put them on the job
of cleaning up society

1794
02:46:08,617 --> 02:46:12,040
Bunty Aur Babli Bunty and Babli

1795
02:46:12,160 --> 02:46:16,954
They maybe two,
but they're too much.
